The paper discusses the use of coordinated sampling for summarizing massive datasets and focuses on the fundamental understanding of the limits and potential of coordination. The paper also proposes a new concept of variance competitiveness. Based on these factors, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.ST (Statistics), and cs.IT (Information Theory).
